      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the pastry",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub the cold butter into the flour and icing sugar until the mixture resembles fine breadcrumbs. Add the egg yolks and just enough cold water to bring the dough together. Press into a disc, wrap, and chill for 30 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Line and blind-bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 180°C conventional (160°C fan). Roll the pastry to 3 mm and line a 23 cm loose-bottomed tart tin. Trim the edges flush, press into the flutes, and chill for 20 minutes. Line with baking paper, fill with baking beans, and bake for 15 minutes. Remove beans and paper and bake for a further 8 to 10 minutes until the base is pale gold and the sides are dry. Cool completely in the tin.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the crème pâtissière",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the milk with the split vanilla pod to just below a simmer; remove the pod. Whisk the egg yolks, sugar, flour, and cornflour together in a bowl until smooth and pale. Pour a third of the hot milk into the egg mixture while whisking, then return everything to the pan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until the cream boils and thickens, about 3 to 4 minutes. Remove from heat and beat in the butter until incorporated. Transfer to a bowl, press cling film directly onto the surface, and refrigerate until fully cold and set, at least 1 hour.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Fill and top",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the chilled crème pâtissière briefly with a spatula to loosen it. Spread it evenly into the cooled tart shell to about 5 mm below the rim. Arrange the raspberries in tight concentric rows, pointed-end up. Serve within 2 hours.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
